Package: TreeBUGS
Type: Package
Title: Hierarchical MPT Modeling using BUGS
Version: 0.2.1
Date: 2015-12-23
Authors@R: c(person("Daniel","Heck",email="heck@uni-mannheim.de",role=c("aut")),
             person("Nina", "Arnold", email="arnold@uni-mannheim.de", role = c("aut")),
             person("Denis", "Arnold", email="denis.arnold@uni-tuebingen.de", role = c("aut","cre")))
Maintainer: Denis Arnold <denis.arnold@uni-tuebingen.de>
Description: Fits hierarchical multinomial processing tree (MPT) models that either assume latent multivariate normal (Klauer, 2010) or indpendent beta distributions (Smith & Batchelder, 2010) for the person parameters. To fit a model, only an .eqn-file as for standard MPT models is required. Moreover, data can either be provided in a comma-separated file (.csv) or directly in R. TreeBUGS then automatically creates a model file and calls JAGS. Fitted models can be analyzed using summary and plotting functions tailored to MPT models.
LazyData: TRUE
Depends:
    R2WinBUGS (>= 2.1),
    R2jags,
    stats,
    graphics,
    utils,
    grDevices
License: GPL (>=2)
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
